# TODO LIST
more timely destruction of unnamed variables
	non-temp locals of an inline
	renaming something *TO* a force_death-ed:
		the force_death is run
		but the variable may get used *after* it
	defer to later
	--
	fundamentally, they're front-end live range annotations
	they provide accurate death points... that have to be maintained during optimization
		but it's more accurate than what we could get in backend
			conditionally assigned locals can be killed in FE
			but in BE... hard to analyze?
	represent scope open/close as hack functions...
	--
	which is easier?
		accurate live range in rcdfsComputeSafeStoreAndVarDeath
			why are we making all the for loops atomic blocks?
				failure to do a proper CFG
		all-the-way maintained FE hint
do not stack-alloc JS-returned arrays
robust serialization
	the most important feature in machine learning code
	matching two pb types
automatically highlight the most useful pieces of errors
	in a user program, not function-ranged
literate-programming-like GL
	tech: global variable indexed by code location
	run time literate for shader composition
	could use it for JS strings?
